                    <h2 id="" class="__title invisible">.</h2>
                    </div>

  
  <h2>Donald and Leah Riddle Prize</h2>
<p>The Donald and Leah Riddle Prize is awarded each year at Commencement to an outstanding graduating senior regardless of major field. The award is based on academic excellence and leadership. The winner receives a bronze medallion and a $1,000 cash prize. The Riddle Prize is made each year in recognition of the former UIC Chancellor Donald Riddle and his wife Leah and honors the Riddles contribution to the campus. The application deadline is typically late March/early April each year. The application is available through UIC SnAP at <a href="http://uic.academicworks.com">uic.academicworks.com</a> and the specific deadline can be found there.</p>
<h2>College Awards</h2>
<p>Many individual colleges recognize outstanding undergraduates in their discipline through various scholarships and awards. Colleges typically offer scholarships and awards in the Spring semester.</p>
<h2>Departmental Awards</h2>
<p>Many individual departments recognize outstanding undergraduates in their discipline through various scholarships and awards. Some departments announce their award winners during convocation ceremonies.</p>



  
